RIYADH: Saudi construction firm Red Sea International, the developer behind the world’s most ambitious regenerative tourism destinations, The Red Sea and AMAALA, has announced the launch of two subsidiaries to boost marine activities for visitors. WAMA and Galaxea will offer activities such as kayaking, canoeing, sailing, and paddle boarding, the Saudi Press Agency reported. It will also hire instructors in sailing, diving, and water sports, as well as captains, technicians, and operators. By 2026, the companies are expected to employ more than 250 people, who will be able to live with their families in Turtle Bay, the firm’s new sustainable residential community. 